            </div>

            <!-- Docker Installation -->
            <div class="tab-content" id="docker-install">
                <h3>Docker Installation</h3>
                <p>The easiest way to get Sayonika running is with Docker. This method handles all dependencies automatically.</p>

                <div class="alert info">
                    <i class="fas fa-info-circle"></i>
                    <div>
                        <strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Make sure you have Docker and Docker Compose installed on your system.
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="step-by-step">
                    <div class="step">
                        <div class="step-number">1</div>
                        <div class="step-content">
                            <h4>Clone the Repository</h4>
                            <div class="code-block">
                                <pre><code>git clone https://github.com/Dynamicaaa/Sayonika.git
cd Sayonika</code></pre>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="step">
                        <div class="step-number">2</div>
                        <div class="step-content">
                            <h4>Configure Environment</h4>
                            <p>Copy the example environment file and configure your settings:</p>
                            <div class="code-block">
                                <pre><code>cp .env.example .env
nano .env</code></pre>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="step">
                        <div class="step-number">3</div>
                        <div class="step-content">
                            <h4>Start with Docker Compose</h4>
                            <div class="code-block">
                                <pre><code>docker-compose up -d</code></pre>
                            </div>
                            <p>This will start Sayonika on <code>http://localhost:3000</code></p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Manual Installation -->
            <div class="tab-content" id="manual-install">
                <h3>Manual Installation</h3>
                <p>For more control over your installation, you can set up Sayonika manually.</p>

                <div class="requirements">
                    <h4>System Requirements</h4>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Node.js 16.0 or higher</li>
                        <li>npm or yarn package manager</li>
                        <li>Git</li>
                        <li>512MB+ RAM</li>
                        <li>1GB+ free disk space</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

                <div class="step-by-step">
                    <div class="step">
                        <div class="step-number">1</div>
                        <div class="step-content">
                            <h4>Install Node.js</h4>
                            <p>Download and install Node.js from <a href="https://nodejs.org" target="_blank">nodejs.org</a> or use a package manager:</p>
                            <div class="code-block">
                                <pre><code># Ubuntu/Debian
sudo apt update
sudo apt install nodejs npm

# macOS with Homebrew
brew install node

# Windows with Chocolatey
choco install nodejs</code></pre>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="step">
                        <div class="step-number">2</div>
                        <div class="step-content">
                            <h4>Clone and Setup</h4>
                            <div class="code-block">
                                <pre><code>git clone https://github.com/Dynamicaaa/Sayonika.git
cd Sayonika
npm install</code></pre>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="step">
                        <div class="step-number">3</div>
                        <div class="step-content">
                            <h4>Configure Environment</h4>
                            <div class="code-block">
                                <pre><code>cp .env.example .env
# Edit .env with your preferred editor</code></pre>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="step">
                        <div class="step-number">4</div>
                        <div class="step-content">
                            <h4>Initialize Database</h4>
                            <div class="code-block">
                                <pre><code>npm run migrate</code></pre>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="step">
                        <div class="step-number">5</div>
                        <div class="step-content">
                            <h4>Start the Server</h4>
                            <div class="code-block">
                                <pre><code>npm start</code></pre>
                            </div>
                            <p>Sayonika will be available at <code>http://localhost:3000</code></p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Development Setup -->
            <div class="tab-content" id="dev-install">
                <h3>Development Setup</h3>
                <p>Set up Sayonika for development with hot reloading and debugging tools.</p>

                <div class="step-by-step">
                    <div class="step">
                        <div class="step-number">1</div>
                        <div class="step-content">
                            <h4>Fork and Clone</h4>
                            <p>Fork the repository on GitHub, then clone your fork:</p>
                            <div class="code-block">
                                <pre><code>git clone https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/Sayonika.git
cd Sayonika
git remote add upstream https://github.com/Dynamicaaa/Sayonika.git</code></pre>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="step">
                        <div class="step-number">2</div>
                        <div class="step-content">
                            <h4>Install Dependencies</h4>
                            <div class="code-block">
                                <pre><code>npm install
# or
yarn install</code></pre>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="step">
                        <div class="step-number">3</div>
                        <div class="step-content">
                            <h4>Development Environment</h4>
                            <div class="code-block">
                                <pre><code>cp .env.example .env.development
# Configure development settings</code></pre>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="step">
                        <div class="step-number">4</div>
                        <div class="step-content">
                            <h4>Start Development Server</h4>
                            <div class="code-block">
                                <pre><code>npm run dev</code></pre>
                            </div>
                            <p>This starts the server with hot reloading and debugging enabled.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="dev-tips">
                    <h4>Development Tips</h4>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Use <code>npm run lint</code> to check code style</li>
                        <li>Run <code>npm test</code> to execute the test suite</li>
                        <li>Use <code>npm run migrate:dev</code> for development database migrations</li>
                        <li>Enable debug mode by setting <code>DEBUG=sayonika:*</code> in your environment</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

